  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What countries can I travel to without an Indian passport?",
  "response": "If you\u2019re an Indian citizen but do not have an Indian passport, your ability to travel internationally depends on the **travel documents you hold**. Here\u2019s a breakdown based on different scenarios:\n\n### 1. **If You Hold a Foreign Passport**\n   - If you\u2019re a citizen of another country and hold a valid passport from that country, you can travel to **any country that allows visa-free or visa-on-arrival entry for that passport**.\n   - For example:\n     - With a **U.S. passport**, you can visit over 180 countries visa-free or with visa-on-arrival.\n     - With a **U.K. passport**, you can visit around 190 countries without a visa.\n   - Check the specific visa requirements for your passport.\n\n### 2. **If You Hold an OCI (Overseas Citizen of India) Card**\n   - **OCI cardholders can travel to India without a visa** and stay indefinitely.\n   - However, **OCI is not a travel document**. You\u2019ll still need a valid passport from your country of citizenship to travel internationally.\n\n### 3. **If You Hold a PIO (Person of Indian Origin) Card**\n   - The PIO card has been merged with the OCI card, and PIO cards are no longer issued.\n   - If you still hold a valid PIO card, it can be used for travel to India until December 31, 2023, after which it will no longer be valid.\n\n### 4. **If You Hold a Refugee Travel Document**\n   - If you\u2019re an Indian citizen with refugee status and hold a **Refugee Travel Document**, you can travel to countries that accept such documents.\n   - However, entry depends on the specific country\u2019s policies. Some countries may require a visa even with a Refugee Travel Document.\n\n### 5. **If You Hold No Valid Travel Document**\n   - Without any valid passport or travel document, **you cannot travel internationally**. You\u2019ll need to obtain a passport from your country of citizenship or a valid travel document from the relevant authorities.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Always check the **entry requirements** of the country you plan to visit, as they vary based on your nationality and travel document.\n- If you\u2019re unsure about your status or travel documents, consult with your country\u2019s embassy or consulate for guidance.\n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like more specific information! \ud83c\udf0d\u2708\ufe0f",
